# Celery + Redis background jobs — rules and skills index

Background-job conventions live in `.cursor/rules/`. Use skills when scaffolding or debugging. All code is self-contained in skills; no external codebase required.

## Full flow (Postgres + Redis + Celery + FastAPI + OpenAI)

End-to-end: HTTP → FastAPI → Celery (Redis broker) → Worker (DB + OpenAI) → PostgreSQL.

```mermaid
flowchart TB
  subgraph client [Client]
    HTTP[HTTP Request]
  end
  subgraph api [FastAPI]
    API[API Routes]
    SessionDep[SessionDep]
  end
  subgraph worker [Celery Worker]
    Task[Task]
    DB[AsyncSession]
    LLM[OpenAI Client]
  end
  subgraph infra [Infrastructure]
    Postgres[(PostgreSQL)]
    Redis[(Redis)]
  end
  HTTP --> API
  API -->|delay| Redis
  Redis --> Task
  Task --> DB
  Task --> LLM
  API --> SessionDep
  SessionDep --> Postgres
  DB --> Postgres
```

**Code reference**: `.cursor/skills/celery-redis-jobs/reference.md` — full code for config, Postgres (storage/database), Redis (worker, zendesk_llm_limiter), ZendeskService, run_async_task. Canonical demo: `.cursor/skills/celery-redis-jobs/zendesk-full-flow.md`.

## Rules (by purpose)

- **celery-worker-tasks** — `.cursor/rules/celery-worker-tasks.mdc` — @worker.task, sync/webhook, chord/chain, run_async_task
- **ai-code-style-reference** — `.cursor/rules/ai-code-style-reference.mdc` — style: minimal change, OOP, env vars, task pattern
- **postgres-setup** — `.cursor/rules/postgres-setup.mdc` — DATABASE_URL, asyncpg, SSL for Azure, AsyncSession
- **openai-setup** — `.cursor/rules/openai-setup.mdc` — OPENAI_API_KEY, base_url, model selection, client usage
- **flyway-migrations** — `.cursor/rules/flyway-migrations.mdc` — Flyway SQL migrations (not Alembic), db/migration, Azure job
- **azure-deploy-full** — `.cursor/rules/azure-deploy-full.mdc` — PostgreSQL, Redis, Container Apps, Key Vault, build→migrate→deploy
- **celery-redis-infra** — `.cursor/rules/celery-redis-infra.mdc` — REDIS_URL local vs Azure rediss, SSL, worker Container App
- **celery-testing-local-azure** — `.cursor/rules/celery-testing-local-azure.mdc` — pytest delay/run mocks, staging smoke, TLS pitfalls
- **toy-greenfield-scaffold** — `.cursor/rules/toy-greenfield-scaffold.mdc` — from-scratch layout, pyproject, worker, tasks
- **toy-docker-local** — `.cursor/rules/toy-docker-local.mdc` — docker-compose Redis, host-run API+worker
- **toy-azure-minimal** — `.cursor/rules/toy-azure-minimal.mdc` — smallest Azure path: rediss, two Container Apps, secrets

